Overview

Angli Xue is a PhD student at Institute for Molecular Bioscience (IMB), The University of Queensland (UQ). He received his bachelor in 2015 from Zhejiang University (ZJU), China, which was followed by a one-year research assistant at the Institute of Bioinformatics, ZJU. He joined Program in Complex Trait Genomics (PCTG) group at UQ in 2016. His research interests are in dissecting the genetic architecture of human complex diseases, performing meta-analysis and integrating multi-omics data to identify associated gene loci and gene regulating mechanisms.
